# Auto-Commit & Push Workflow

After completing each logical file group below, AUTOMATICALLY run git add, commit, and push without asking.

## Commit Format

Always use conventional commits: `type(scope): description`

Types: `feat`, `fix`, `chore`, `docs`, `refactor`, `test`
Scopes: `scaffold`, `db`, `auth`, `extension`, `api`, `ui`, `dashboard`, `pages`, `business`, `devops`, `docs`, `email`, `stripe`, `cron`, `tests`, `seo`

## Auto-Push Trigger Groups

After finishing each group, run:
```
git add -A && git commit -m "feat(scope): description" && git push origin main
```

| Group | Files | Commit Message |
|-------|-------|----------------|
| 1 - Scaffold | package.json, tsconfig, tailwind, .gitignore, .env.example, next.config.mjs | `feat(scaffold): initialize Next.js 14 with TypeScript and Tailwind` |
| 2 - Database | prisma/schema.prisma, prisma/seed.ts, docker-compose.yml, src/lib/prisma.ts | `feat(db): add Prisma schema, seed data, and Docker Postgres` |
| 3 - Auth | src/auth.ts, middleware.ts, src/lib/rate-limit.ts, src/lib/api-error.ts, src/lib/cors.ts | `feat(auth): configure NextAuth v5, middleware, rate limiter, and security helpers` |
| 4 - Extension | extension/* | `feat(extension): add Chrome extension with privacy-first tracking` |
| 5 - API Routes | src/app/api/** | `feat(api): implement all API routes with validation and auth` |
| 6 - Components | src/components/** | `feat(ui): add shadcn/ui base and custom components` |
| 7 - Dashboard | src/app/dashboard/** | `feat(dashboard): build dashboard pages with usage tracking and analytics` |
| 8 - Pages | src/app/page.tsx, src/app/pricing, src/app/auth, src/app/privacy, src/app/terms, src/app/cookies | `feat(pages): add landing, pricing, auth, and legal pages` |
| 9 - Business Logic | src/lib/overlap-detector.ts, src/lib/stripe.ts, src/lib/email.ts, src/emails/** | `feat(business): implement overlap detection, Stripe, and email services` |
| 10 - DevOps | Dockerfile, docker-compose.yml (prod), nginx/**, scripts/**, .github/workflows/** | `feat(devops): add Docker, nginx, deploy scripts, and CI/CD workflows` |
| 11 - Docs | CLAUDE.md, README.md | `docs(docs): add CLAUDE reference and README` |

## Rules

- NEVER skip a push after completing a group
- NEVER commit .env files (only .env.example)
- If git push fails (no remote yet), run `git add -A && git commit -m "..."` only and note remote isn't set up yet
- Use `git push origin main` (not force push)
